name: Climbing fiber multi-innervation of mouse Purkinje dendrites with arborization common to human
citation: Busch, Silas (2023) Climbing fiber multi-innervation of mouse Purkinje dendrites with arborization common to human (Version draft) [Data set]. DANDI archive. https://doi.org/10.80507/dandi.123456/0.123456.1234
description:
These datasets contain processed (not raw) data and code used in the final analyses of experiments involving slice electrophysiology, immunohistochemistry, and in vivo calcium imaging from mice. The accompanying R markdown code provides column header names for data sheets lacking headers.

The study investigates the relation between dendrite morphology and climbing fiber multi-innervation in mature mice and the distribution of dendrite morphologies in both human and mouse.
